FBIS4-35751 "drnes107_r_94005" FBIS-NES-94-107 Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 India Home Minister Sees `Improvement' in Kashmir Home Minister Sees `Improvement' in Kashmir BK0206130194 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 GMT 2 Jun 94 BK0206130194 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] The minister of state for home, Mr. Rajesh Pilot, says there are distinct signs of improvement in the law and order situation in the Kashmir Valley. Addressing a meeting at Gurez near Kashmir, Mr. Pilot reiterated that the center is ready to hold talks with anyone if it aims to bring back normalcy to Jammu and Kashmir, but he warned that the government will never give up its efforts to crush militant activities and their designs to undermine the nation's unity and integrity.
